DATA CLOUD
Refresh History of Data Streams and Data Lake Objects

Data Cloud provides record-level statistics of the data ingested by data streams and records processed into a data lake object (DLO).

Data Stream Refresh History

View the Refresh History tab on the data stream record home for the record statistics. After the initial ingestion of data into Data Cloud, a data stream pulls new data based on specific schedules and refreshes the data.

The data refresh information for each data stream can vary based on the connector that the data stream ingests the data from. The table lists the general information available for a data stream.

FIELD NAME	DESCRIPTION
Refresh Date	The date and time of the last data refresh. It is displayed in your org's time zone.
Refresh Mode	The way data is refreshed during each cycle, such as a full or incremental refresh.
Duration	Time taken for the data refresh.
Status	The status of the last refresh.
Records Processed	The number of records processed during the refresh cycle.
Records Added	The number of records ingested or added during the refresh cycle.
Records Removed	The number of records deleted from Data Cloud during a refresh cycle.
Data Lake Object Refresh History

View the Refresh History tab on the DLO record home for the record-level statistics. The statistics are aggregated in hourly time windows, and the refresh history is kept for up to 20 days. The information is available for DLOs that are used by data streams and data transforms.

If there are no changes to data records in a DLO during the time window, no details are listed on the Refresh History tab.

FIELD NAME	DESCRIPTION
Start Time	The beginning time of an hourly time window for which the record-level statistics are aggregated. It is displayed in your org time zone.
End Time	The end time of an hourly time window for aggregating the record-level statistics. It is displayed in your org time zone.
Total Records	Total number of records in the DLO at the end of the time window.
Records Added	Number of records that are added to the DLO during the time window.
Records Updated	Number of records that are updated in the DLO during the time window.
Records Removed	The number of records that are physically deleted from the DLO during the time window.
